The paper deals with the polyhedral structure of the matching polytope, which is a fundamental problem in combinatorial optimization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses information-theoretic concepts to analyze perturbations of slack matrices, which suggests a possible connection to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also discusses the polyhedral inapproximability of the matching polytope, which suggests a possible connection to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the correlation polytope, which is a problem in game theory, suggesting a possible connection to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
